id: pm-e02lgu
title: "Quota-aware branch protection: external AI review limits must never block merges"
description: "Keep deterministic repository-owned quality and security gates required, but remove quota-limited external AI review contexts from branch protection whenever their free quota is exhausted or the service is unavailable. PR review bots remain advisory and must still be triggered, reviewed, reacted to, and documented when available."
type: Task
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:ci","area:github",quota-safety,review-automation
created_at: "2026-07-21T18:06:39.089Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T18:05:28.537Z"
author: codex-derived-context-20260721
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "Live main protection does not require Greptile, CodeRabbit, Gemini, Sourcery, or other quota-limited AI review contexts; deterministic build, coverage, compatibility, smoke, security, platform, Codecov, and CodeFactor checks remain required; PR #633 auto-merges without an admin bypass; the exact before/after required-check inventory and quota evidence are recorded."
parent: pm-92if
risk: medium
confidence: high
